By Bolaji Buhari Lagos – A member of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) Presidential Campaign Council, Mr Akin Osuntokun, on Wednesday said that he could only wish Nigeria well following the re-election of President  Muhammadu Buhari. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that the Independent
National Electoral Commission (INEC) had early on Wednesday announced
President Muhammadu Buhari as the  winner of the  Feb. 23 Presidential
election. INEC Chairman, Prof. Mahmoud Yakubu, while announcing the results in
Abuja, said that Buhari, the presidential candidate of the All
Progressives Congress (APC),  polled 15,191,847 votes to defeat Alhaji
Atiku Abubakar of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) who scored 11,255,978 votes. Osuntokun reacting to the result in a telephone interview told the
News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) that  he had no comments but to wish the
country well. “I have no comments but to wish the country the best of luck. That is all I can say, I wish the country well,” he said. Osuntokun, who served as  the Political Adviser to former President
Olusegun Obasanjo, also declined to comment on Atiku’s decision to
challenge the results in court. London - Nigeria’s dollar-denominated government bonds rose to 5-7 month highs on Wednesday after President… PDP has rejected the results of last Saturday’s Presidential and National Assembly elections being announced… By Solomon Asowata Lagos - Ex-workers of Nigeria Airways Ltd. on Wednesday hailed the re-election…